The paper deals with the problem of ranking a set of items based on pairwise preferences and feature information. This falls under the broad area of machine learning, specifically in the subfield of ranking and recommendation systems. The use of matrix completion and side information also suggests a connection to the subfield of collaborative filtering. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of matrix completion and low-rank models also suggests a connection to the subfield of linear algebra and optimization, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
